257
00:13:29.000 --> 00:13:30.000
Don't be Rick-dikulous, Morty.

258
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:32.000
W-w-will you stop saying that? It's stupid.

259
00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:34.000
Take his Morty away.

260
00:13:34.000 --> 00:13:35.000
Come with me.

261
00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:36.000
Yeah, gladly.

262
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:38.000
Jeez, man. Rick's, huh?

263
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:44.000
Hey, man, you seem to know how this place works. Is there any way we could shut down that grid and rescue all those Morty's outside?

264
00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:48.000
It would be pointless. Morty's have no chance of defeating a Rick.

265
00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:50.000
In here.

266
00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:01.000
Ah, isn't it beautiful?

267
00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:04.000
Yeah, yeah. It looks like payday at Neverland Ranch in here.

268
00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:05.000
Zing!

269
00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:07.000
That guy got it.

270
00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:10.000
Rick, quiet. You're missing my symphony.

271
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:16.000
Hey, I'll take it over Mumford and Sons. Zip!

272
00:14:17.000 --> 00:14:20.000
This guy is on it. He's not laughing at your dumb jokes, Rick.

273
00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:23.000
That's just a random noise it makes every ten seconds.

274
00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:30.000
You see, Rick, you're not as clever as you think you are. I wanted you to find me.

275
00:14:30.000 --> 00:14:32.000
We're not so different, you and I.

276
00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:33.000
Yeah, duh!

277
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:38.000
See this right here, Rick? I crunched the numbers. I created a spectrum of all the Rick's.

278
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.000
I listed them out from most evil to least evil.

279
00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:45.000
Here's where I am. And look at right here's where you are, Rick.

280
00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:47.000
This guy right here, super weird.

281
00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:51.000
I get it. So you want me to team up with you to take down the Council of Rick's, right?

282
00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:53.000
Is that where you're going with this? Because that's where I'd be going.

283
00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:56.000
Please. I think I'm doing pretty good on my own.

284
00:14:56.000 --> 00:15:00.000
I'm simply gonna download the contents of your brain and then kill you.

285
00:15:02.000 --> 00:15:07.000
Okay, if we had a little more titanium nitrate and just a tad of chlorophyte tartrate...

286
00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:10.000
Ovenless brownies!

287
00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:16.000
Hmm. It's incredible what a gifted mind can accomplish when priorities are in order.

288
00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:21.000
Well, come on. I can't take all the credit, Jerry. It was your idea. Come here, Jerry.

289
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:29.000
Hey, come here. I want to show you something.

290
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:34.000
Okay, look, everybody makes fun of me for getting these, but you're a genius scientist. What do you think?

291
00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:37.000
There's little R2-D2s where the George Washington should be.

292
00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:43.000
You know, Jerry, I'm not gonna tell you that these will increase in value or even hold their current value.

293
00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:48.000
The truth is, you bought them because you like them. They have value to you. That's what matters.

294
00:15:51.000 --> 00:15:53.000
How long are you staying?

295
00:15:53.000 --> 00:15:55.000
Until we find your Rick.

296
00:15:55.000 --> 00:15:59.000
I found mine. I found mine.

297
00:16:01.000 --> 00:16:02.000
Help!

298
00:16:02.000 --> 00:16:06.000
There is no escape, my son. We will find our peace in the next world.

299
00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:09.000
So what? You're just gonna give up?

300
00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:17.000
We're giving in to the power of the one true Morty. One day he will return. Praise the one true Morty.

301
00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:26.000
All right, Mortys. Listen up. My name is Morty Smith from Earth Dimension C-137.

302
00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:31.000
I know you're scared because I'm scared, but that's no reason to accept our fate. We're Mortys.

303
00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:36.000
We're not defined by our relationships to Rick. Our destiny is our own.

304
00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:41.000
This sounds like something the one true Morty might say. I'm sick of being a human shield.

305
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:46.000
I want to be a gardener. I want to write really crazy, intense action novels.

306
00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:48.000
I'm more than just a hammer.

307
00:16:48.000 --> 00:16:50.000
He is the one true Morty.

308
00:16:50.000 --> 00:16:52.000
We're the one true Morty.

309
00:16:52.000 --> 00:16:54.000
Keep it down.

310
00:16:54.000 --> 00:16:56.000
No!

311
00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:09.000
You've lived quite a life, Rick. It's a real shame you're not gonna be around to see it through.

312
00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:20.000
You're crying over a Morty?

313
00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:22.000
No, I'm just allergic to dipshits.

314
00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:29.000
Ugh, pathetic. We both know that if there's any truth in the universe, it's that Rick's don't care about Mortys.

315
00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:37.000
Do your worst, you little bastards! Kill me! Do it! Do it!

316
00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:42.000
Morty, thank God! Get me out of this! Come on!

317
00:17:42.000 --> 00:17:44.000
You're lucky I'm not a Rick.

318
00:17:44.000 --> 00:17:47.000
Point taken, but this is no time for arcs.

319
00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:55.000
Yeah, hello?

320
00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:58.000
Hey, what do me and O.J. not have in common?

321
00:17:58.000 --> 00:17:59.000
Huh? Who is this?

322
00:17:59.000 --> 00:18:02.000
I found the real killer, bitch! Get over here!

323
00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:08.000
Yo, Ding Dong, we're done here. Time to go.

324
00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:12.000
Well, Cherry, I guess this means goodbye.

325
00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:18.000
What? What does it have to? You look just like Rick. We could maybe, you know, get rid of him.

326
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:23.000
I'm not saying kill him necessarily. I'm also not saying necessarily not kill him, but...

327
00:18:23.000 --> 00:18:28.000
Jerry, we both know it wouldn't work. It's time to go back to our lives.

328
00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:31.000
I love you, Jerry. I love you.

329
00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:50.000
What's going to happen to all these Mortys?

330
00:18:50.000 --> 00:18:55.000
They'll go back to their families, attend school regularly, play video games, date girls, poor little Rickless bastards.

331
00:18:56.000 --> 00:19:01.000
EarthRick C-137, the council apologizes for its false accusation, and in the way of reparations, for our terrible mistake,

332
00:19:01.000 --> 00:19:06.000
we would like to compensate you with this voucher for what you have done to us.

333
00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:08.000
I'm sorry, but I'm sorry.

334
00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:10.000
I'm sorry, but I'm sorry.

335
00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:12.000
I'm sorry, but I'm sorry.

336
00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:14.000
I'm sorry, but I'm sorry.

337
00:19:14.000 --> 00:19:22.000
It's a terrible mistake. We would like to compensate you with this voucher for a free replacement Morty in the event that your current Morty should...

338
00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:26.000
Uh, guys? Not a good time. Come on, Morty. Let's hit it.

339
00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:35.000
Is it time for arcs yet, Rick? I did a pretty good job back there for a human cloaking device. Saved your ass.

340
00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:38.000
All right, Morty. Don't break an arm jerking yourself off.

341
00:19:38.000 --> 00:19:43.000
Man, I can't believe you, Rick. That right there. That was a great opportunity to show a little humanity, you know?

342
00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:45.000
To connect with me a little.

343
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:48.000
Hey, Morty, you want connection? Go be part of some stupid club like all those dumb ricks.

344
00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:51.000
You know, maybe I don't connect because I'm the rickest Rick there is.

345
00:19:51.000 --> 00:19:57.000
And, you know, it would go without saying that the rickest Rick would have the mortiest Morty.

346
00:19:57.000 --> 00:19:59.000
It would go without saying, huh?

347
00:19:59.000 --> 00:20:01.000
Yeah, it would. Did you hear me say it?

348
00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:04.000
Nah. The mortiest Morty.

349
00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:09.000
Just don't get too big for your loafers, Buster Brown. A cocky Morty can lead to some big problems.

350
00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:11.000
It can be a real bad thing for everybody.

351
00:20:11.000 --> 00:20:13.000
Yeah, how's that?

352
00:20:13.000 --> 00:20:15.000
I'll explain when you're older.

353
00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:18.000
What a mess.

354
00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:21.000
Pride cometh before the fall. I guess he got what he deserved.

355
00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:23.000
What is that?

356
00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:25.000
Hand me the laser defibrillator.

357
00:20:25.000 --> 00:20:27.000
Hey, guys, can I help?

358
00:20:27.000 --> 00:20:30.000
No. Go clean the toilets. Maybe you'll make friends with some turds.

359
00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:33.000
You make us ashamed to be ourselves.

360
00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:36.000
My God.

361
